genresAdvancedInfo.name: canadian underground hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Canadian Underground Hip Hop is a subgenre of hip hop music that is often associated with independent artists who have a strong DIY ethic. It is characterized by its focus on social and political issues, as well as its rejection of mainstream hip hop culture. Canadian Underground Hip Hop artists often have a strong following in their local communities, and many have gained international recognition.
